    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Maerua deckenii are infusion, tincture, decoction, tea, and Maerua decoction. Infusion is made by steeping Maerua deckenii leaves in hot water to release its bioactive compounds, primarily flavonoids and alkaloids. Decoction is a preparation method where Maerua deckenii roots and bark are boiled in water to extract its secondary metabolites, including phenolic acids and glycosides. Tincture is a concentrated liquid preparation made by soaking Maerua deckenii roots and leaves in a solvent, such as ethanol or glycerin, to obtain its bioactive compounds. Maerua decoction is a traditional preparation method used in African herbal medicine, where the plant's roots and leaves are boiled together to treat various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and skin diseases.",
